                             ===Issue===                                                                                            
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Summary                                                                                             
                                                                                                                                    
                             A libFuzzer session terminated with an ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout message. The                        
                             fuzzing process exceeded its allotted execution time without completing, causing                       
                             libFuzzer to abort the run.                                                                            
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Description                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                    
                             - Issue Statement                                                                                      
                               libFuzzer reported a timeout error, indicating that one or more test cases executed                  
                             by the fuzz target did not complete within the configured time limit.                                  
                                                                                                                                    
                             - Vulnerability Type                                                                                   
                               No specific vulnerability is named in the issue. The timeout suggests potential                      
                             hangs or longrunning code paths, but the report itself does not classify it as a                      
                             security flaw.                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                    
                             - Key Observations and Findings                                                                        
                                The timeout occurs during the fuzzing harnesss execution, but the harness merely                  
                             serves as an entry point for feeding inputs to the code under test.                                    
                                Any unbounded loops, blocking calls, or resource waits in the target code can lead                 
                             to this timeout.                                                                                       
                                The error prevents the fuzzer from progressing to other inputs or achieving deeper                 
                             coverage.                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             - Code Areas for Investigation                                                                         
                               1. Fuzzing Harness                                                                                   
                                   Confirm that the harness invokes the target functions cleanly and does not                      
                             introduce its own delays.                                                                              
                               2. Target Code Paths                                                                                 
                                   Review loops, recursion, and state machines for termination conditions.                         
                                   Identify any I/O operations, synchronization primitives, or external calls that                 
                             may block indefinitely.                                                                                
                               3. Fuzzing Configuration                                                                             
                                   Inspect libFuzzer flags (e.g., timeout) and their values to understand the                     
                             threshold that was exceeded.                                                                           
                                                                                                                                    
                             A thorough review of these components will provide a holistic view of why the fuzzing                  
                             process is timing out.                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                   
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                         
                             <issue>

                             244:                        if (!(value instanceof COSBase))                                           
                             245:                        {                                                                          
                             246:                            LOG.warn("Unexpected token in inline image dictionary                  
                             at offset {}",                                                                                         
                             247:                                    source.isClosed() ? "EOF" :                                    
                             source.getPosition());                                                                                 
                             248:                            break;                                                                 
                             249:                        }                                                                          
                             250:                        imageParams.setItem( (COSName)nextToken, (COSBase)value );                 
                             251:                    }                                                                              
                             252:                    //final token will be the image data, maybe??                                  
                             253:                    if (nextToken instanceof Operator)                                             
                             254:                    {                                                                              
                             255:                        Operator imageData = (Operator) nextToken;                                 
                             256:                        if (imageData.getImageData() == null ||                                    
                             imageData.getImageData().length == 0)                                                                  
                             257:                        {                                                                          
                             258:                            LOG.warn("empty inline image at stream offset {}",                     
                             259:                                    source.getPosition());                                         
                             260:                        }                                                                          
                             261:                        beginImageOP.setImageData(imageData.getImageData());                       
                             262:                    }                                                                              
                             263:                }                                                                                  
                             264:                return beginImageOP;                                                               
                             265:            case 'I':                                                                              
                             266:                //Special case for ID operator                                                     
                             267:                String id = Character.toString((char) source.read()) + (char)                      
                             source.read();                                                                                         
                             268:                if (!id.equals(OperatorName.BEGIN_INLINE_IMAGE_DATA))                              
                             269:                {                                                                                  
                             270:                    long currentPosition = source.getPosition();                                   
                             271:                    close();                                                                       
                             272:                    throw new IOException( "Error: Expected operator 'ID'                          
                             actual='" + id +                                                                                       
                             273:                            "' at stream offset " + currentPosition);                              
                             274:                }                                                                                  
                             275:                ByteArrayOutputStream imageData = new ByteArrayOutputStream();                     
                             276:                // skip one line break (CR, LF or CRLF) or any one-byte whitespace                 
                             277:                if (!skipLinebreak() && isWhitespace())                                            
                             278:                {                                                                                  
                             279:                    // pull off the whitespace character                                           
                             280:                    source.read();                                                                 
                             281:                }                                                                                  
                             282:                int lastByte = source.read();                                                      
                             283:                int currentByte = source.read();                                                   
                             284:                // PDF spec is kinda unclear about this. Should a whitespace                       
                             285:                // always appear before EI? Not sure, so that we just read                         
                             286:                // until EI<whitespace>.                                                           
                             287:                // Be aware not all kind of whitespaces are allowed here. see                      
                             PDFBOX-1561                                                                                            
                             288:                while( !(lastByte == 'E' &&                                                        
                             289:                         currentByte == 'I' &&                                                     
                             290:                         hasNextSpaceOrReturn() &&                                                 
                             291:                    hasNoFollowingBinData()) &&                                                    
                             292:                    !isEOF())                                                                      
                             293:                {                                                                                  
                             294:                    imageData.write( lastByte );                                                   
                             295:                    lastByte = currentByte;                                                        
                             296:                    currentByte = source.read();                                                   
                             297:                }                                                                                  
                             298:                // the EI operator isn't unread, as it won't be processed anyway                   
                             299:                Operator beginImageDataOP = Operator                                               
                             300:                        .getOperator(OperatorName.BEGIN_INLINE_IMAGE_DATA);                        
                             301:                // save the image data to the operator, so that it can be accessed                 
                             later                                                                                                  
                             302:                beginImageDataOP.setImageData(imageData.toByteArray());                            
                             303:                return beginImageDataOP;                                                           
                             304:            case ']':                                                                              
                             305:                // some ']' around without its previous '['                                        
                             306:                // this means a PDF is somewhat corrupt but we will continue to                    
                             parse.                                                                                                 
                             307:                source.read();                                                                     
                             308:                                                                                                   
                             309:                // must be a better solution than null...                                          
                             310:                return COSNull.NULL;                                                               
                             311:            default:                                                                               
                             312:                // we must be an operator                                                          
                             313:                String operator = readOperator().trim();                                           
                             314:                if (!operator.isEmpty())                                                           
                             315:                {                                                                                  
                             316:                    return Operator.getOperator(operator);                                         
                             317:                }                                                                                  
                             318:        }                                                                                          
                             319:        return null;                                                                               
                             320:    }                                                                                              
                             321:                                                                                                   
                             322:    /**                                                                                            
                             323:     * Looks up an amount of bytes if they contain only ASCII characters (no                       
                             324:     * control sequences etc.), and that these ASCII characters begin with a                       
                             325:     * sequence of 1-3 non-blank characters between blanks                                         
                             326:     *                                                                                             
                             327:     * @return <code>true</code> if next bytes are probably printable ASCII                        
                             328:     * characters starting with a PDF operator, otherwise <code>false</code>                       
                             329:     */                                                                                            
                             330:    private boolean hasNoFollowingBinData() throws IOException                                     
                             331:    {                                                                                              
                             332:        // as suggested in PDFBOX-1164                                                             
                             333:        final int readBytes = source.read(binCharTestArr, 0,                                       
                             MAX_BIN_CHAR_TEST_LENGTH);                                                                             
                             334:        boolean noBinData = true;                                                                  
                             335:        int startOpIdx = -1;                                                                       
                             336:        int endOpIdx = -1;                                                                         
                             337:        String s = "";                                                                             
                             338:                                                                                                   
                             339:        LOG.debug("String after EI: '{}'", () -> new String(binCharTestArr));                      
                             340:                                                                                                   
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BaseParser.java:460-550                               
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             460:            if (!isLF(next))                                                                       
                             461:            {                                                                                      
                             462:                source.rewind(1);                                                                  
                             463:            }                                                                                      
                             464:        }                                                                                          
                             465:        else if (!isLF(linebreak))                                                                 
                             466:        {                                                                                          
                             467:            return false;                                                                          
                             468:        }                                                                                          
                             469:        return true;                                                                               
                             470:    }                                                                                              
                             471:                                                                                                   
                             472:    /**                                                                                            
                             473:     * This is really a bug in the Document creators code, but it caused a crash                   
                             in PDFBox, the first bug was in this                                                                   
                             474:     * format: /Title ( (5) /Creator which was patched in 1 place.                                 
                             475:     *                                                                                             
                             476:     * However it missed the case where the number of opening and closing                          
                             parenthesis isn't balanced                                                                             
                             477:     *                                                                                             
                             478:     * The second bug was in this format /Title (c:\) /Producer                                    
                             479:     *                                                                                             
                             480:     * @param bracesParameter the number of braces currently open.                                 
                             481:     *                                                                                             
                             482:     * @return the corrected value of the brace counter                                            
                             483:     * @throws IOException                                                                         
                             484:     */                                                                                            
                             485:    private int checkForEndOfString(final int bracesParameter) throws IOException                  
                             486:    {                                                                                              
                             487:        if (bracesParameter == 0)                                                                  
                             488:        {                                                                                          
                             489:            return 0;                                                                              
                             490:        }                                                                                          
                             491:        // Check the next 3 bytes if available                                                     
                             492:        byte[] nextThreeBytes = new byte[3];                                                       
                             493:        int amountRead = source.read(nextThreeBytes);                                              
                             494:        if (amountRead > 0)                                                                        
                             495:        {                                                                                          
                             496:            source.rewind(amountRead);                                                             
                             497:        }                                                                                          
                             498:        if (amountRead < 3)                                                                        
                             499:        {                                                                                          
                             500:            return bracesParameter;                                                                
                             501:        }                                                                                          
                             502:        // The following cases are valid indicators for the end of the string                      
                             503:        // 1. Next line contains another COSObject: CR + LF + '/'                                  
                             504:        // 2. COSDictionary ends in the next line: CR + LF + '>'                                   
                             505:        // 3. Next line contains another COSObject: LF + '/'                                       
                             506:        // 4. COSDictionary ends in the next line: LF + '>'                                        
                             507:        // 5. Next line contains another COSObject: CR + '/'                                       
                             508:        // 6. COSDictionary ends in the next line: CR + '>'                                        
                             509:        if (((isCR(nextThreeBytes[0]) || isLF(nextThreeBytes[0]))                                  
                             510:                && (nextThreeBytes[1] == '/' || nextThreeBytes[1] == '>')) //                      
                             511:                || //                                                                              
                             512:                (isCR(nextThreeBytes[0]) && isLF(nextThreeBytes[1])                                
                             513:                        && (nextThreeBytes[2] == '/' || nextThreeBytes[2] == '>'))                 
                             //                                                                                                     
                             514:        )                                                                                          
                             515:        {                                                                                          
                             516:            return 0;                                                                              
                             517:        }                                                                                          
                             518:        return bracesParameter;                                                                    
                             519:    }                                                                                              
                             520:                                                                                                   
                             521:    /**                                                                                            
                             522:     * This will parse a PDF string.                                                               
                             523:     *                                                                                             
                             524:     * @return The parsed PDF string.                                                              
                             525:     *                                                                                             
                             526:     * @throws IOException If there is an error reading from the stream.                           
                             527:     */                                                                                            
                             528:    protected COSString parseCOSString() throws IOException                                        
                             529:    {                                                                                              
                             530:        char nextChar = (char) source.read();                                                      
                             531:        if (nextChar == '<')                                                                       
                             532:        {                                                                                          
                             533:            return parseCOSHexString();                                                            
                             534:        }                                                                                          
                             535:        else if (nextChar != '(')                                                                  
                             536:        {                                                                                          
                             537:            throw new IOException( "parseCOSString string should start with '(' or                 
                             '<' and not '" +                                                                                       
                             538:                    nextChar + "' at offset " + source.getPosition());                             
                             539:        }                                                                                          
                             540:                                                                                                   
                             541:        ByteArrayOutputStream out = new ByteArrayOutputStream();                                   
                             542:                                                                                                   
                             543:        // This is the number of braces read                                                       
                             544:        int braces = 1;                                                                            
                             545:        int c = source.read();                                                                     
                             546:        while( braces > 0 && c != -1)                                                              
                             547:        {                                                                                          
                             548:            char ch = (char)c;                                                                     
                             549:            int nextc = -2; // not yet read                                                        
                             550:                                                                                                   
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFStreamParser.java:1-200                            
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             1:/*                                                                                                   
                             2: * Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more                                
                             3: * contributor license agreements.  See the NOTICE file distributed with                             
                             4: * this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership.                               
                             5: * The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0                           
                             6: * (the "License"); you may not use this file except in compliance with                              
                             7: * the License.  You may obtain a copy of the License at                                             
                             8: *                                                                                                   
                             9: *      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0                                                   
                             10: *                                                                                                  
                             11: * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software                              
                             12: * distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,                                
                             13: * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.                         
                             14: * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and                              
                             15: * limitations under the License.                                                                   
                             16: */                                                                                                 
                             17:package org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser;                                                                
                             18:                                                                                                    
                             19:import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;                                                               
                             20:import java.io.IOException;                                                                         
                             21:import java.util.ArrayList;                                                                         
                             22:import java.util.List;                                                                              
                             23:import org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger;                                                             
                             24:import org.apache.logging.log4j.LogManager;                                                         
                             25:import org.apache.pdfbox.contentstream.PDContentStream;                                             
                             26:import org.apache.pdfbox.contentstream.operator.Operator;                                           
                             27:import org.apache.pdfbox.contentstream.operator.OperatorName;                                       
                             28:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSBase;                                                               
                             29:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSBoolean;                                                            
                             30:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSDictionary;                                                         
                             31:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSName;                                                               
                             32:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSNull;                                                               
                             33:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSNumber;                                                             
                             34:import org.apache.pdfbox.io.RandomAccessReadBuffer;                                                 
                             35:                                                                                                    
                             36:/**                                                                                                 
                             37: * This will parse a PDF byte stream and extract operands and such.                                 
                             38: *                                                                                                  
                             39: * @author Ben Litchfield                                                                           
                             40: */                                                                                                 
                             41:public class PDFStreamParser extends BaseParser                                                     
                             42:{                                                                                                   
                             43:    /**                                                                                             
                             44:     * Log instance.                                                                                
                             45:     */                                                                                             
                             46:    private static final Logger LOG = LogManager.getLogger(PDFStreamParser.class);                  
                             47:                                                                                                    
                             48:    private static final int MAX_BIN_CHAR_TEST_LENGTH = 10;                                         
                             49:    private final byte[] binCharTestArr = new byte[MAX_BIN_CHAR_TEST_LENGTH];                       
                             50:                                                                                                    
                             51:    /**                                                                                             
                             52:     * Constructor.                                                                                 
                             53:     *                                                                                              
                             54:     * @param pdContentstream The content stream to parse.                                          
                             55:     * @throws IOException If there is an error initializing the stream.                            
                             56:     */                                                                                             
                             57:    public PDFStreamParser(PDContentStream pdContentstream) throws IOException                      
                             58:    {                                                                                               
                             59:        super(pdContentstream.getContentsForStreamParsing());                                       
                             60:    }                                                                                               
                             61:                                                                                                    
                             62:    /**                                                                                             
                             63:     * Constructor.                                                                                 
                             64:     *                                                                                              
                             65:     * @param bytes the bytes to parse.                                                             
                             66:     */                                                                                             
                             67:    public PDFStreamParser(byte[] bytes)                                                            
                             68:    {                                                                                               
                             69:        super(new RandomAccessReadBuffer(bytes));                                                   
                             70:    }                                                                                               
                             71:                                                                                                    
                             72:    /**                                                                                             
                             73:     * This will parse all the tokens in the stream. This will close the stream                     
                             when it is finished parsing.                                                                           
                             74:     *                                                                                              
                             75:     * @return All of the tokens in the stream.                                                     
                             76:     * @throws IOException If there is an error while parsing the stream.                           
                             77:     */                                                                                             
                             78:    public List<Object> parse() throws IOException                                                  
                             79:    {                                                                                               
                             80:        List<Object> streamObjects = new ArrayList<>(100);                                          
                             81:        Object token;                                                                               
                             82:        while( (token = parseNextToken()) != null )                                                 
                             83:        {                                                                                           
                             84:            streamObjects.add( token );                                                             
                             85:        }                                                                                           
                             86:        return streamObjects;                                                                       
                             87:    }                                                                                               
                             88:                                                                                                    
                             89:    /**                                                                                             
                             90:     * This will parse the next token in the stream.                                                
                             91:     *                                                                                              
                             92:     * @return The next token in the stream or null if there are no more tokens in                  
                             the stream.                                                                                            
                             93:     *                                                                                              
                             94:     * @throws IOException If an io error occurs while parsing the stream.                          
                             95:     */                                                                                             
                             96:    public Object parseNextToken() throws IOException                                               
                             97:    {                                                                                               
                             98:        if (source.isClosed())                                                                      
                             99:        {                                                                                           
                             100:            return null;                                                                           
                             101:        }                                                                                          
                             102:        skipSpaces();                                                                              
                             103:        if (source.isEOF())                                                                        
                             104:        {                                                                                          
                             105:            close();                                                                               
                             106:            return null;                                                                           
                             107:        }                                                                                          
                             108:        char c = (char) source.peek();                                                             
                             109:        switch (c)                                                                                 
                             110:        {                                                                                          
                             111:            case '<':                                                                              
                             112:                // pull off first left bracket                                                     
                             113:                source.read();                                                                     
                             114:                                                                                                   
                             115:                // check for second left bracket                                                   
                             116:                c = (char) source.peek();                                                          
                             117:                                                                                                   
                             118:                // put back first bracket                                                          
                             119:                source.rewind(1);                                                                  
                             120:                                                                                                   
                             121:                if (c == '<')                                                                      
                             122:                {                                                                                  
                             123:                    try                                                                            
                             124:                    {                                                                              
                             125:                        return parseCOSDictionary(true);                                           
                             126:                    }                                                                              
                             127:                    catch (IOException exception)                                                  
                             128:                    {                                                                              
                             129:                        LOG.warn("Stop reading invalid dictionary from content                     
                             stream at offset {}",                                                                                  
                             130:                                source.getPosition());                                             
                             131:                        close();                                                                   
                             132:                        return null;                                                               
                             133:                    }                                                                              
                             134:                }                                                                                  
                             135:                else                                                                               
                             136:                {                                                                                  
                             137:                    return parseCOSString();                                                       
                             138:                }                                                                                  
                             139:            case '[':                                                                              
                             140:                // array                                                                           
                             141:                try                                                                                
                             142:                {                                                                                  
                             143:                    return parseCOSArray();                                                        
                             144:                }                                                                                  
                             145:                catch (IOException exception)                                                      
                             146:                {                                                                                  
                             147:                    LOG.warn("Stop reading invalid array from content stream at                    
                             offset {}",                                                                                            
                             148:                            source.getPosition());                                                 
                             149:                    close();                                                                       
                             150:                    return null;                                                                   
                             151:                }                                                                                  
                             152:            case '(':                                                                              
                             153:                // string                                                                          
                             154:                return parseCOSString();                                                           
                             155:            case '/':                                                                              
                             156:                // name                                                                            
                             157:                return parseCOSName();                                                             
                             158:            case 'n':                                                                              
                             159:                // null                                                                            
                             160:                String nullString = readString();                                                  
                             161:                if( nullString.equals( "null") )                                                   
                             162:                {                                                                                  
                             163:                    return COSNull.NULL;                                                           
                             164:                }                                                                                  
                             165:                else                                                                               
                             166:                {                                                                                  
                             167:                    return Operator.getOperator(nullString);                                       
                             168:                }                                                                                  
                             169:            case 't':                                                                              
                             170:            case 'f':                                                                              
                             171:                String next = readString();                                                        
                             172:                if( next.equals( "true" ) )                                                        
                             173:                {                                                                                  
                             174:                    return COSBoolean.TRUE;                                                        
                             175:                }                                                                                  
                             176:                else if( next.equals( "false" ) )                                                  
                             177:                {                                                                                  
                             178:                    return COSBoolean.FALSE;                                                       
                             179:                }                                                                                  
                             180:                else                                                                               
                             181:                {                                                                                  
                             182:                    return Operator.getOperator(next);                                             
                             183:                }                                                                                  
                             184:            case '0':                                                                              
                             185:            case '1':                                                                              
                             186:            case '2':                                                                              
                             187:            case '3':                                                                              
                             188:            case '4':                                                                              
                             189:            case '5':                                                                              
                             190:            case '6':                                                                              
                             191:            case '7':                                                                              
                             192:            case '8':                                                                              
                             193:            case '9':                                                                              
                             194:            case '-':                                                                              
                             195:            case '+':                                                                              
                             196:            case '.':                                                                              
                             197:                /* We will be filling buf with the rest of the number.  Only                       
                             198:                 * allow 1 "." and "-" and "+" at start of number. */                              
                             199:                StringBuilder buf = new StringBuilder();                                           
                             200:                buf.append( c );                                                                   
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java:1-200                           
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             1:/*                                                                                                   
                             2: * Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more                                
                             3: * contributor license agreements.  See the NOTICE file distributed with                             
                             4: * this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership.                               
                             5: * The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0                           
                             6: * (the "License"); you may not use this file except in compliance with                              
                             7: * the License.  You may obtain a copy of the License at                                             
                             8: *                                                                                                   
                             9: *      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0                                                   
                             10: *                                                                                                  
                             11: * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software                              
                             12: * distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,                                
                             13: * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.                         
                             14: * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and                              
                             15: * limitations under the License.                                                                   
                             16: */                                                                                                 
                             17:package org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser;                                                                
                             18:                                                                                                    
                             19:import java.io.IOException;                                                                         
                             20:import java.util.ArrayList;                                                                         
                             21:import java.util.HashMap;                                                                           
                             22:import java.util.List;                                                                              
                             23:import java.util.Map;                                                                               
                             24:import java.util.Map.Entry;                                                                         
                             25:import java.util.stream.Collectors;                                                                 
                             26:                                                                                                    
                             27:import org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger;                                                             
                             28:import org.apache.logging.log4j.LogManager;                                                         
                             29:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSArray;                                                              
                             30:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSBase;                                                               
                             31:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSDictionary;                                                         
                             32:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSDocument;                                                           
                             33:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSName;                                                               
                             34:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSObject;                                                             
                             35:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSObjectKey;                                                          
                             36:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSStream;                                                             
                             37:import org.apache.pdfbox.io.RandomAccessRead;                                                       
                             38:import org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.XrefTrailerResolver.XRefType;                                    
                             39:import org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.encryption.ProtectionPolicy;                                       
                             40:import org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.encryption.SecurityHandler;                                        
                             41:                                                                                                    
                             42:/**                                                                                                 
                             43: * Brute force parser to be used as last resort if a malformed pdf can't be read.                   
                             44: */                                                                                                 
                             45:public class BruteForceParser                                                                       
                             46:{                                                                                                   
                             47:    private static final char[] XREF_TABLE = { 'x', 'r', 'e', 'f' };                                
                             48:    private static final char[] XREF_STREAM = { '/', 'X', 'R', 'e', 'f' };                          
                             49:                                                                                                    
                             50:    private static final long MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET = 6;                                            
                             51:                                                                                                    
                             52:    /**                                                                                             
                             53:     * EOF-marker.                                                                                  
                             54:     */                                                                                             
                             55:    private static final char[] EOF_MARKER = { '%', '%', 'E', 'O', 'F' };                           
                             56:    /**                                                                                             
                             57:     * obj-marker.                                                                                  
                             58:     */                                                                                             
                             59:    private static final char[] OBJ_MARKER = { 'o', 'b', 'j' };                                     
                             60:                                                                                                    
                             61:    /**                                                                                             
                             62:     * trailer-marker.                                                                              
                             63:     */                                                                                             
                             64:    private static final char[] TRAILER_MARKER = { 't', 'r', 'a', 'i', 'l', 'e',                    
                             'r' };                                                                                                 
                             65:                                                                                                    
                             66:    /**                                                                                             
                             67:     * ObjStream-marker.                                                                            
                             68:     */                                                                                             
                             69:    private static final char[] OBJ_STREAM = { '/', 'O', 'b', 'j', 'S', 't', 'm' };                 
                             70:                                                                                                    
                             71:    private static final Logger LOG = LogManager.getLogger(BruteForceParser.class);                 
                             72:                                                                                                    
                             73:    /**                                                                                             
                             74:     * Contains all found objects of a brute force search.                                          
                             75:     */                                                                                             
                             76:    private final Map<COSObjectKey, Long> bfSearchCOSObjectKeyOffsets = new                         
                             HashMap<>();                                                                                           
                             77:                                                                                                    
                             78:    private boolean bfSearchTriggered = false;                                                      
                             79:                                                                                                    
                             80:    private final COSParser parser;                                                                 
                             81:    private final COSDocument document;                                                             
                             82:    private final RandomAccessRead source;                                                          
                             83:                                                                                                    
                             84:    /**                                                                                             
                             85:     * Constructor. Triggers a brute force search for all objects of the document.                  
                             86:     *                                                                                              
                             87:     * @param cosDocument the corresponding COS document                                            
                             88:     * @param cosParser the COSParser to be used for reading the pdf                                
                             89:     *                                                                                              
                             90:     * @throws IOException if the source data could not be read                                     
                             91:     */                                                                                             
                             92:    public BruteForceParser(COSDocument cosDocument, COSParser cosParser) throws                    
                             IOException                                                                                            
                             93:    {                                                                                               
                             94:        document = cosDocument;                                                                     
                             95:        parser = cosParser;                                                                         
                             96:        source = parser.source;                                                                     
                             97:    }                                                                                               
                             98:                                                                                                    
                             99:    /**                                                                                             
                             100:     * Indicates wether the brute force search for objects was triggered.                          
                             101:     *                                                                                             
                             102:     * @return true if the search was triggered                                                    
                             103:     */                                                                                            
                             104:    public boolean bfSearchTriggered()                                                             
                             105:    {                                                                                              
                             106:        return bfSearchTriggered;                                                                  
                             107:    }                                                                                              
                             108:                                                                                                   
                             109:    /**                                                                                            
                             110:     * Returns all found objects of a brute force search.                                          
                             111:     *                                                                                             
                             112:     * @return map containing all found objects of a brute force search                            
                             113:     *                                                                                             
                             114:     * @throws IOException if something went wrong                                                 
                             115:     *                                                                                             
                             116:     */                                                                                            
                             117:    protected Map<COSObjectKey, Long> getBFCOSObjectOffsets() throws IOException                   
                             118:    {                                                                                              
                             119:        if (!bfSearchTriggered)                                                                    
                             120:        {                                                                                          
                             121:            bfSearchTriggered = true;                                                              
                             122:            bfSearchForObjects();                                                                  
                             123:        }                                                                                          
                             124:        return bfSearchCOSObjectKeyOffsets;                                                        
                             125:    }                                                                                              
                             126:                                                                                                   
                             127:    /**                                                                                            
                             128:     * Brute force search for every object in the pdf.                                             
                             129:     *
