                             130:     * @throws IOException if something went wrong                                                 
                             131:     */                                                                                            
                             132:    private void bfSearchForObjects() throws IOException                                           
                             133:    {                                                                                              
                             134:        long lastEOFMarker = bfSearchForLastEOFMarker();                                           
                             135:        long originOffset = source.getPosition();                                                  
                             136:        long currentOffset = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET;                                                
                             137:        long lastObjectId = Long.MIN_VALUE;                                                        
                             138:        int lastGenID = Integer.MIN_VALUE;                                                         
                             139:        long lastObjOffset = Long.MIN_VALUE;                                                       
                             140:        char[] endobjString = "ndo".toCharArray();                                                 
                             141:        char[] endobjRemainingString = "bj".toCharArray();                                         
                             142:        boolean endOfObjFound = false;                                                             
                             143:        do                                                                                         
                             144:        {                                                                                          
                             145:            source.seek(currentOffset);                                                            
                             146:            int nextChar = source.read();                                                          
                             147:            currentOffset++;                                                                       
                             148:            if (BaseParser.isWhitespace(nextChar) && parser.isString(OBJ_MARKER))                  
                             149:            {                                                                                      
                             150:                long tempOffset = currentOffset - 2;                                               
                             151:                source.seek(tempOffset);                                                           
                             152:                int genID = source.peek();                                                         
                             153:                // is the next char a digit?                                                       
                             154:                if (BaseParser.isDigit(genID))                                                     
                             155:                {                                                                                  
                             156:                    genID -= 48;                                                                   
                             157:                    tempOffset--;                                                                  
                             158:                    source.seek(tempOffset);                                                       
                             159:                    if (parser.isWhitespace())                                                     
                             160:                    {                                                                              
                             161:                        while (tempOffset > MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET &&                               
                             parser.isWhitespace())                                                                                 
                             162:                        {                                                                          
                             163:                            source.seek(--tempOffset);                                             
                             164:                        }                                                                          
                             165:                        boolean objectIDFound = false;                                             
                             166:                        while (tempOffset > MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET &&                               
                             parser.isDigit())                                                                                      
                             167:                        {                                                                          
                             168:                            source.seek(--tempOffset);                                             
                             169:                            objectIDFound = true;                                                  
                             170:                        }                                                                          
                             171:                        if (objectIDFound)                                                         
                             172:                        {                                                                          
                             173:                            source.read();                                                         
                             174:                            long objectId = parser.readObjectNumber();                             
                             175:                            if (lastObjOffset > 0)                                                 
                             176:                            {                                                                      
                             177:                                // add the former object ID only if there was a                    
                             subsequent object ID                                                                                   
                             178:                                bfSearchCOSObjectKeyOffsets.put(                                   
                             179:                                        new COSObjectKey(lastObjectId, lastGenID),                 
                             lastObjOffset);                                                                                        
                             180:                            }                                                                      
                             181:                            lastObjectId = objectId;                                               
                             182:                            lastGenID = genID;                                                     
                             183:                            lastObjOffset = tempOffset + 1;                                        
                             184:                            currentOffset += OBJ_MARKER.length - 1;                                
                             185:                            endOfObjFound = false;                                                 
                             186:                        }                                                                          
                             187:                    }                                                                              
                             188:                }                                                                                  
                             189:            }                                                                                      
                             190:            // check for "endo" as abbreviation for "endobj", as the pdf may be                    
                             cut off                                                                                                
                             191:            // in the middle of the keyword, see PDFBOX-3936.                                      
                             192:            // We could possibly implement a more intelligent algorithm if                         
                             necessary                                                                                              
                             193:            else if (nextChar == 'e' && parser.isString(endobjString))                             
                             194:            {                                                                                      
                             195:                currentOffset += endobjString.length;                                              
                             196:                source.seek(currentOffset);                                                        
                             197:                if (parser.isEOF())                                                                
                             198:                {                                                                                  
                             199:                    endOfObjFound = true;                                                          
                             200:                }                                                                                  
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/COSParser.java:200-260                                
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             200:                setEOFLookupRange(Integer.parseInt(eofLookupRangeStr));                            
                             201:            }                                                                                      
                             202:            catch (NumberFormatException nfe)                                                      
                             203:            {                                                                                      
                             204:                LOG.warn(                                                                          
                             205:                        "System property " + SYSPROP_EOFLOOKUPRANGE + " does not                   
                             contain an integer value, but: '{}'",                                                                  
                             206:                        eofLookupRangeStr);                                                        
                             207:            }                                                                                      
                             208:        }                                                                                          
                             209:        document = new COSDocument(streamCacheCreateFunction, this);                               
                             210:    }                                                                                              
                             211:                                                                                                   
                             212:    /**                                                                                            
                             213:     * Sets how many trailing bytes of PDF file are searched for EOF marker and                    
                             'startxref' marker. If not set we use                                                                  
                             214:     * default value {@link #DEFAULT_TRAIL_BYTECOUNT}.                                             
                             215:     *                                                                                             
                             216:     * <p>We check that new value is at least 16. However for practical use cases                  
                             this value should not be lower than                                                                    
                             217:     * 1000; even 2000 was found to not be enough in some cases where some                         
                             trailing garbage like HTML snippets followed                                                           
                             218:     * the EOF marker.</p>                                                                         
                             219:     *                                                                                             
                             220:     * <p>                                                                                         
                             221:     * In case system property {@link #SYSPROP_EOFLOOKUPRANGE} is defined this                     
                             value will be set on initialization but                                                                
                             222:     * can be overwritten later.                                                                   
                             223:     * </p>                                                                                        
                             224:     *                                                                                             
                             225:     * @param byteCount number of trailing bytes                                                   
                             226:     */                                                                                            
                             227:    public void setEOFLookupRange(int byteCount)                                                   
                             228:    {                                                                                              
                             229:        if (byteCount > 15)                                                                        
                             230:        {                                                                                          
                             231:            readTrailBytes = byteCount;                                                            
                             232:        }                                                                                          
                             233:    }                                                                                              
                             234:                                                                                                   
                             235:    /**                                                                                            
                             236:     * Read the trailer information and provide a COSDictionary containing the                     
                             trailer information.                                                                                   
                             237:     *                                                                                             
                             238:     * @return a COSDictionary containing the trailer information                                  
                             239:     * @throws IOException if something went wrong                                                 
                             240:     */                                                                                            
                             241:    protected COSDictionary retrieveTrailer() throws IOException                                   
                             242:    {                                                                                              
                             243:        COSDictionary trailer = null;                                                              
                             244:        boolean rebuildTrailer = false;                                                            
                             245:        try                                                                                        
                             246:        {                                                                                          
                             247:            // parse startxref                                                                     
                             248:            // TODO FDF files don't have a startxref value, so that rebuildTrailer                 
                             is triggered                                                                                           
                             249:            long startXRefOffset = getStartxrefOffset();                                           
                             250:            if (startXRefOffset > -1)                                                              
                             251:            {                                                                                      
                             252:                XrefParser xrefParser = new XrefParser(this);                                      
                             253:                trailer = xrefParser.parseXref(document, startXRefOffset);                         
                             254:                xrefTable.putAll(xrefParser.getXrefTable());                                       
                             255:            }                                                                                      
                             256:            else                                                                                   
                             257:            {                                                                                      
                             258:                rebuildTrailer = isLenient();                                                      
                             259:            }                                                                                      
                             260:        }                                                                                          
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/XrefParser.java:1-200                                 
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             1:/*                                                                                                   
                             2: * Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more                                
                             3: * contributor license agreements.  See the NOTICE file distributed with                             
                             4: * this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership.

                             8: *                                                                                                   
                             9: *      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0                                                   
                             10: *                                                                                                  
                             11: * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software                              
                             12: * distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,                                
                             13: * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.                         
                             14: * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and                              
                             15: * limitations under the License.                                                                   
                             16: */                                                                                                 
                             17:package org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser;                                                                
                             18:                                                                                                    
                             19:import java.io.IOException;                                                                         
                             20:import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;                                                           
                             21:import java.util.HashMap;                                                                           
                             22:import java.util.HashSet;                                                                           
                             23:import java.util.Map;                                                                               
                             24:import java.util.Optional;                                                                          
                             25:import java.util.Map.Entry;                                                                         
                             26:                                                                                                    
                             27:import org.apache.logging.log4j.LogManager;                                                         
                             28:import org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger;                                                             
                             29:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSDictionary;                                                         
                             30:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSDocument;                                                           
                             31:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSName;                                                               
                             32:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSObjectKey;                                                          
                             33:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSStream;                                                             
                             34:import org.apache.pdfbox.io.RandomAccessRead;                                                       
                             35:import org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser.XrefTrailerResolver.XRefType;                                    
                             36:                                                                                                    
                             37:/**                                                                                                 
                             38: * Parser to be used to read the cross reference table of a pdf. It is either a                     
                             simple table or a stream.                                                                              
                             39: */                                                                                                 
                             40:public class XrefParser                                                                             
                             41:{                                                                                                   
                             42:    private static final Logger LOG = LogManager.getLogger(XrefParser.class);                       
                             43:                                                                                                    
                             44:    private static final int X = 'x';                                                               
                             45:    private static final char[] XREF_TABLE = { 'x', 'r', 'e', 'f' };                                
                             46:    private static final char[] STARTXREF = { 's', 't', 'a', 'r', 't', 'x', 'r',                    
                             'e', 'f' };                                                                                            
                             47:                                                                                                    
                             48:    /**                                                                                             
                             49:     * Collects all Xref/trailer objects and resolves them into single                              
                             50:     * object using startxref reference.                                                            
                             51:     */                                                                                             
                             52:    private XrefTrailerResolver xrefTrailerResolver = new XrefTrailerResolver();                    
                             53:                                                                                                    
                             54:    private final COSParser parser;                                                                 
                             55:    private final RandomAccessRead source;                                                          
                             56:                                                                                                    
                             57:    /**                                                                                             
                             58:     * Default constructor.                                                                         
                             59:     *                                                                                              
                             60:     * @param cosParser the parser to be used to read the pdf.                                      
                             61:     *                                                                                              
                             62:     */                                                                                             
                             63:    public XrefParser(COSParser cosParser)                                                          
                             64:    {                                                                                               
                             65:        parser = cosParser;                                                                         
                             66:        source = parser.source;                                                                     
                             67:    }                                                                                               
                             68:                                                                                                    
                             69:    /**                                                                                             
                             70:     * Returns the resulting cross reference table.                                                 
                             71:     *                                                                                              
                             72:     * @return                                                                                      
                             73:     */                                                                                             
                             74:    public Map<COSObjectKey, Long> getXrefTable()                                                   
                             75:    {                                                                                               
                             76:        return xrefTrailerResolver.getXrefTable();                                                  
                             77:    }                                                                                               
                             78:                                                                                                    
                             79:    /**                                                                                             
                             80:     * Parses cross reference tables.                                                               
                             81:     *                                                                                              
                             82:     * @param document the corresponding COS document of the pdf.                                   
                             83:     * @param startXRefOffset start offset of the first table                                       
                             84:     *                                                                                              
                             85:     * @return the trailer dictionary                                                               
                             86:     *                                                                                              
                             87:     * @throws IOException if something went wrong                                                  
                             88:     */                                                                                             
                             89:    public COSDictionary parseXref(COSDocument document, long startXRefOffset)                      
                             throws IOException                                                                                     
                             90:    {                                                                                               
                             91:        source.seek(startXRefOffset);                                                               
                             92:        long startXrefOffset = Math.max(0, parseStartXref());                                       
                             93:        // check the startxref offset                                                               
                             94:        long fixedOffset = checkXRefOffset(startXrefOffset);                                        
                             95:        if (fixedOffset > -1)                                                                       
                             96:        {                                                                                           
                             97:            startXrefOffset = fixedOffset;                                                          
                             98:        }                                                                                           
                             99:        document.setStartXref(startXrefOffset);                                                     
                             100:        long prev = startXrefOffset;                                                               
                             101:        //lastPrev prevents potential infinite loops in crafted files                              
                             102:        long lastPrev = -1;                                                                        
                             103:        // ---- parse whole chain of xref tables/object streams using PREV                         
                             reference                                                                                              
                             104:        COSDictionary trailer = null;                                                              
                             105:        while (prev > 0 && prev != lastPrev)                                                       
                             106:        {                                                                                          
                             107:            lastPrev = prev;                                                                       
                             108:            // seek to xref table                                                                  
                             109:            source.seek(prev);                                                                     
                             110:            // skip white spaces                                                                   
                             111:            parser.skipSpaces();                                                                   
                             112:            // -- parse xref                                                                       
                             113:            if (source.peek() == X)                                                                
                             114:            {                                                                                      
                             115:                // xref table and trailer                                                          
                             116:                // use existing parser to parse xref table                                         
                             117:                if (!parseXrefTable(prev) || !parseTrailer())                                      
                             118:                {                                                                                  
                             119:                    throw new IOException("Expected trailer object at offset "                     
                             120:                            + source.getPosition());                                               
                             121:                }                                                                                  
                             122:                trailer = xrefTrailerResolver.getCurrentTrailer();                                 
                             123:                // check for a XRef stream, it may contain some object ids of                      
                             compressed objects                                                                                     
                             124:                if(trailer.containsKey(COSName.XREF_STM))                                          
                             125:                {                                                                                  
                             126:                    int streamOffset = trailer.getInt(COSName.XREF_STM);                           
                             127:                    // check the xref stream reference                                             
                             128:                    fixedOffset = checkXRefOffset(streamOffset);                                   
                             129:                    if (fixedOffset > -1 && fixedOffset != streamOffset)                           
                             130:                    {                                                                              
                             131:                        LOG.warn("/XRefStm offset {} is incorrect, corrected to                    
                             {}", streamOffset,                                                                                     
                             132:                                fixedOffset);                                                      
                             133:                        streamOffset = (int)fixedOffset;                                           
                             134:                        trailer.setInt(COSName.XREF_STM, streamOffset);                            
                             135:                    }                                                                              
                             136:                    if (streamOffset > 0)                                                          
                             137:                    {                                                                              
                             138:                        source.seek(streamOffset);                                                 
                             139:                        parser.skipSpaces();                                                       
                             140:                        try                                                                        
                             141:                        {                                                                          
                             142:                            parseXrefObjStream(prev, false);                                       
                             143:                            document.setHasHybridXRef();                                           
                             144:                        }                                                                          
                             145:                        catch (IOException ex)                                                     
                             146:                        {                                                                          
                             147:                            LOG.error("Failed to parse /XRefStm at offset " +                      
                             streamOffset, ex);                                                                                     
                             148:                        }                                                                          
                             149:                    }                                                                              
                             150:                    else                                                                           
                             151:                    {                                                                              
                             152:                        LOG.error("Skipped XRef stream due to a corrupt offset:                    
                             {}", streamOffset);                                                                                    
                             153:                    }                                                                              
                             154:                }                                                                                  
                             155:                prev = trailer.getLong(COSName.PREV);                                              
                             156:            }                                                                                      
                             157:            else                                                                                   
                             158:            {                                                                                      
                             159:                // parse xref stream                                                               
                             160:                prev = parseXrefObjStream(prev, true);                                             
                             161:                trailer = xrefTrailerResolver.getCurrentTrailer();                                 
                             162:            }                                                                                      
                             163:            if (prev > 0)                                                                          
                             164:            {                                                                                      
                             165:                // check the xref table reference                                                  
                             166:                fixedOffset = checkXRefOffset(prev);                                               
                             167:                if (fixedOffset > -1 && fixedOffset != prev)                                       
                             168:                {                                                                                  
                             169:                    prev = fixedOffset;                                                            
                             170:                    trailer.setLong(COSName.PREV, prev);                                           
                             171:                }                                                                                  
                             172:            }                                                                                      
                             173:            if (prev == lastPrev)                                                                  
                             174:            {                                                                                      
                             175:                throw new IOException("/Prev loop at offset " + prev);                             
                             176:            }                                                                                      
                             177:        }                                                                                          
                             178:        // ---- build valid xrefs out of the xref chain                                            
                             179:        xrefTrailerResolver.setStartxref(startXrefOffset);                                         
                             180:        trailer = xrefTrailerResolver.getTrailer();                                                
                             181:        document.setTrailer(trailer);                                                              
                             182:        document.setIsXRefStream(XRefType.STREAM ==                                                
                             xrefTrailerResolver.getXrefType());                                                                    
                             183:        // check the offsets of all referenced objects                                             
                             184:        checkXrefOffsets();                                                                        
                             185:        // copy xref table                                                                         
                             186:        document.addXRefTable(xrefTrailerResolver.getXrefTable());                                 
                             187:                                                                                                   
                             188:        // remember the highest XRef object number to avoid it being reused in                     
                             incremental saving                                                                                     
                             189:        Optional<Long> maxValue = document.getXrefTable().keySet().stream() //                     
                             190:                .map(COSObjectKey::getNumber) //                                                   
                             191:                .reduce(Long::max);                                                                
                             192:        document.setHighestXRefObjectNumber(maxValue.isPresent() ? maxValue.get()                  
                             : 0);                                                                                                  
                             193:                                                                                                   
                             194:        return trailer;                                                                            
                             195:    }                                                                                              
                             196:                                                                                                   
                             197:    /**                                                                                            
                             198:     * This will parse the trailer from the stream and add it to the state.                        
                             199:     *                                                                                             
                             200:     * @return false on parsing error                                                              
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/XrefTrailerResolver.java:1-200                        
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             1:/*                                                                                                   
                             2: * Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more                                
                             3: * contributor license agreements.  See the NOTICE file distributed with                             
                             4: * this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership.                               
                             5: * The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0                           
                             6: * (the "License"); you may not use this file except in compliance with                              
                             7: * the License.  You may obtain a copy of the License at                                             
                             8: *                                                                                                   
                             9: *      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0                                                   
                             10: *                                                                                                  
                             11: * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software                              
                             12: * distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,                                
                             13: * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.                         
                             14: * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and                              
                             15: * limitations under the License.                                                                   
                             16: */                                                                                                 
                             17:package org.apache.pdfbox.pdfparser;                                                                
                             18:                                                                                                    
                             19:import java.util.ArrayList;                                                                         
                             20:import java.util.Collections;                                                                       
                             21:import java.util.HashMap;                                                                           
                             22:import java.util.HashSet;                                                                           
                             23:import java.util.List;                                                                              
                             24:import java.util.Map;                                                                               
                             25:import java.util.Set;                                                                               
                             26:import java.util.SortedSet;                                                                         
                             27:import java.util.TreeSet;                                                                           
                             28:                                                                                                    
                             29:import org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger;                                                             
                             30:import org.apache.logging.log4j.LogManager;                                                         
                             31:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSDictionary;                                                         
                             32:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSName;                                                               
                             33:import org.apache.pdfbox.cos.COSObjectKey;                                                          
                             34:                                                                                                    
                             35:/**                                                                                                 
                             36: * This class will collect all XRef/trailer objects and creates correct                             
                             37: * xref/trailer information after all objects are read using startxref                              
                             38: * and 'Prev' information (unused XRef/trailer objects are discarded).                              
                             39: *                                                                                                  
                             40: * In case of missing startxref or wrong startxref pointer all                                      
                             41: * XRef/trailer objects are used to create xref table / trailer dictionary                          
                             42: * in order they occur.                                                                             
                             43: *                                                                                                  
                             44: * For each new xref object/XRef stream method {@link #nextXrefObj(long, XRefType)}                 
                             45: * must be called with start byte position. All following calls to                                  
                             46: * {@link #setXRef(COSObjectKey, long)} or {@link #setTrailer(COSDictionary)}                       
                             47: * will add the data for this byte position.                                                        
                             48: *                                                                                                  
                             49: * After all objects are parsed the startxref position must be provided                             
                             50: * using {@link #setStartxref(long)}. This is used to build the chain of                            
                             51: * active xref/trailer objects used for creating document trailer and xref table.                   
                             52: *                                                                                                  
                             53: * @author Timo Bhme                                                                               
                             54: */                                                                                                 
                             55:public class XrefTrailerResolver                                                                    
                             56:{                                                                                                   
                             57:                                                                                                    
                             58:    /**                                                                                             
                             59:     * A class which represents a xref/trailer object.                                              
                             60:     */                                                                                             
                             61:    private static class XrefTrailerObj                                                             
                             62:    {                                                                                               
                             63:        protected COSDictionary trailer = null;                                                     
                             64:                                                                                                    
                             65:        private XRefType xrefType;                                                                  
                             66:                                                                                                    
                             67:        private final Map<COSObjectKey, Long> xrefTable = new HashMap<>();                          
                             68:                                                                                                    
                             69:        /**                                                                                         
                             70:         *  Default constructor.                                                                    
                             71:         */                                                                                         
                             72:        private XrefTrailerObj()                                                                    
                             73:        {                                                                                           
                             74:            xrefType = XRefType.TABLE;                                                              
                             75:        }                                                                                           
                             76:                                                                                                    
                             77:        public void reset()                                                                         
                             78:        {                                                                                           
                             79:            xrefTable.clear();                                                                      
                             80:        }                                                                                           
                             81:    }                                                                                               
                             82:                                                                                                    
                             83:    /**                                                                                             
                             84:     * The XRefType of a trailer.                                                                   
                             85:     */                                                                                             
                             86:    public enum XRefType                                                                            
                             87:    {                                                                                               
                             88:        /**                                                                                         
                             89:         * XRef table type.                                                                         
                             90:         */                                                                                         
                             91:        TABLE,                                                                                      
                             92:        /**                                                                                         
                             93:         * XRef stream type.                                                                        
                             94:         */                                                                                         
                             95:        STREAM                                                                                      
                             96:    }                                                                                               
                             97:                                                                                                    
                             98:    private final Map<Long, XrefTrailerObj> bytePosToXrefMap = new HashMap<>();                     
                             99:    private XrefTrailerObj curXrefTrailerObj   = null;                                              
                             100:    private XrefTrailerObj resolvedXrefTrailer = null;                                             
                             101:                                                                                                   
                             102:    /** Log instance. */                                                                           
                             103:    private static final Logger LOG =                                                              
                             LogManager.getLogger(XrefTrailerResolver.class );                                                      
                             104:                                                                                                   
                             105:    /**                                                                                            
                             106:     * Returns the first trailer if at least one exists.                                           
                             107:     *                                                                                             
                             108:     * @return the first trailer or null                                                           
                             109:     */                                                                                            
                             110:    public final COSDictionary getFirstTrailer()                                                   
                             111:    {                                                                                              
                             112:        if (bytePosToXrefMap.isEmpty())                                                            
                             113:        {                                                                                          
                             114:            return null;                                                                           
                             115:        }                                                                                          
                             116:        Set<Long> offsets = bytePosToXrefMap.keySet();                                             
                             117:        SortedSet<Long> sortedOffset = new TreeSet<>(offsets);                                     
                             118:        return bytePosToXrefMap.get(sortedOffset.first()).trailer;                                 
                             119:    }                                                                                              
                             120:                                                                                                   
                             121:    /**                                                                                            
                             122:     * Returns the last trailer if at least one exists.                                            
                             123:     *                                                                                             
                             124:     * @return the last trailer ir null                                                            
                             125:     */                                                                                            
                             126:    public final COSDictionary getLastTrailer()                                                    
                             127:    {                                                                                              
                             128:        if (bytePosToXrefMap.isEmpty())                                                            
                             129:        {                                                                                          
                             130:            return null;                                                                           
                             131:        }                                                                                          
                             132:        Set<Long> offsets = bytePosToXrefMap.keySet();                                             
                             133:        SortedSet<Long> sortedOffset = new TreeSet<>(offsets);                                     
                             134:        return bytePosToXrefMap.get(sortedOffset.last()).trailer;                                  
                             135:    }                                                                                              
                             136:                                                                                                   
                             137:    /**                                                                                            
                             138:     * Returns the count of trailers.                                                              
                             139:     *                                                                                             
                             140:     * @return the count of trailers.                                                              
                             141:     */                                                                                            
                             142:    public final int getTrailerCount()                                                             
                             143:    {                                                                                              
                             144:        return bytePosToXrefMap.size();                                                            
                             145:    }                                                                                              
                             146:                                                                                                   
                             147:    /**                                                                                            
                             148:     * Signals that a new XRef object (table or stream) starts.                                    
                             149:     * @param startBytePos the offset to start at                                                  
                             150:     * @param type the type of the Xref object                                                     
                             151:     */                                                                                            
                             152:    public void nextXrefObj( final long startBytePos, XRefType type )                              
                             153:    {                                                                                              
                             154:        curXrefTrailerObj = new XrefTrailerObj();                                                  
                             155:        bytePosToXrefMap.put(startBytePos, curXrefTrailerObj);                                     
                             156:        curXrefTrailerObj.xrefType = type;                                                         
                             157:    }                                                                                              
                             158:                                                                                                   
                             159:    /**                                                                                            
                             160:     * Returns the XRefTxpe of the resolved trailer.                                               
                             161:     *                                                                                             
                             162:     * @return the XRefType or null.                                                               
                             163:     */                                                                                            
                             164:    public XRefType getXrefType()                                                                  
                             165:    {                                                                                              
                             166:        return ( resolvedXrefTrailer == null ) ? null :                                            
                             resolvedXrefTrailer.xrefType;                                                                          
                             167:    }                                                                                              
                             168:                                                                                                   
                             169:    /**                                                                                            
                             170:     * Populate XRef HashMap of current XRef object.                                               
                             171:     * Will add an Xreftable entry that maps ObjectKeys to byte offsets in the                     
                             file.                                                                                                  
                             172:     * @param objKey The objkey, with id and gen numbers                                           
                             173:     * @param offset The byte offset in this file                                                  
                             174:     */                                                                                            
                             175:    public void setXRef( COSObjectKey objKey, long offset )                                        
                             176:    {                                                                                              
                             177:        if ( curXrefTrailerObj == null )                                                           
                             178:        {                                                                                          
                             179:            // should not happen...                                                                
                             180:            LOG.warn("Cannot add XRef entry for '{}' because XRef start was not                    
                             signalled.",                                                                                           
                             181:                    objKey.getNumber());                                                           
                             182:            return;                                                                                
                             183:        }                                                                                          
                             184:        // PDFBOX-3506 check before adding to the map, to avoid entries from the                   
                             table being                                                                                            
                             185:        // overwritten by obsolete entries in hybrid files (/XRefStm entry)                        
                             186:        if (!curXrefTrailerObj.xrefTable.containsKey(objKey) )                                     
                             187:        {                                                                                          
                             188:            curXrefTrailerObj.xrefTable.put(objKey, offset);                                       
                             189:        }                                                                                          
                             190:    }                                                                                              
                             191:                                                                                                   
                             192:    /**                                                                                            
                             193:     * Adds trailer information for current XRef object.                                           
                             194:     *                                                                                             
                             195:     * @param trailer the current document trailer dictionary                                      
                             196:     */                                                                                            
                             197:    public void setTrailer( COSDictionary trailer )                                                
                             198:    {                                                                                              
                             199:        if ( curXrefTrailerObj == null )                                                           
                             200:        {                                                                                          
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/COSParser.java:300-360                                
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             300:     * <code>startxref</code>.                                                                     
                             301:     *                                                                                             
                             302:     * @return the offset of StartXref                                                             
                             303:     * @throws IOException If something went wrong.                                                
                             304:     */                                                                                            
                             305:    private long getStartxrefOffset() throws IOException                                           
                             306:    {                                                                                              
                             307:        byte[] buf;                                                                                
                             308:        long skipBytes;                                                                            
                             309:        // read trailing bytes into buffer                                                         
                             310:        try                                                                                        
                             311:        {                                                                                          
                             312:            final int trailByteCount = (fileLen < readTrailBytes) ? (int) fileLen                  
                             : readTrailBytes;                                                                                      
                             313:            buf = new byte[trailByteCount];                                                        
                             314:            skipBytes = fileLen - trailByteCount;                                                  
                             315:            source.seek(skipBytes);                                                                
                             316:            int off = 0;                                                                           
                             317:            int readBytes;                                                                         
                             318:            while (off < trailByteCount)                                                           
                             319:            {                                                                                      
                             320:                readBytes = source.read(buf, off, trailByteCount - off);                           
                             321:                // in order to not get stuck in a loop we check readBytes (this
