                             ```                                                                                                    
                             should never happen)                                                                                   
                             322:                if (readBytes < 1)                                                                 
                             323:                {                                                                                  
                             324:                    throw new IOException(                                                         
                             325:                            "No more bytes to read for trailing buffer, but                        
                             expected: "                                                                                            
                             326:                                    + (trailByteCount - off));                                     
                             327:                }                                                                                  
                             328:                off += readBytes;                                                                  
                             329:            }                                                                                      
                             330:        }                                                                                          
                             331:        finally                                                                                    
                             332:        {                                                                                          
                             333:            source.seek(0);                                                                        
                             334:        }                                                                                          
                             335:        // find last '%%EOF'                                                                       
                             336:        int bufOff = lastIndexOf(EOF_MARKER, buf, buf.length);                                     
                             337:        if (bufOff < 0)                                                                            
                             338:        {                                                                                          
                             339:            if (isLenient)                                                                         
                             340:            {                                                                                      
                             341:                // in lenient mode the '%%EOF' isn't needed                                        
                             342:                bufOff = buf.length;                                                               
                             343:                LOG.debug("Missing end of file marker '{}'", new                                   
                             String(EOF_MARKER));                                                                                   
                             344:            }                                                                                      
                             345:            else                                                                                   
                             346:            {                                                                                      
                             347:                throw new IOException("Missing end of file marker '" + new                         
                             String(EOF_MARKER) + "'");                                                                             
                             348:            }                                                                                      
                             349:        }                                                                                          
                             350:        // find last startxref preceding EOF marker                                                
                             351:        bufOff = lastIndexOf(STARTXREF, buf, bufOff);                                              
                             352:        if (bufOff < 0)                                                                            
                             353:        {                                                                                          
                             354:            throw new IOException("Missing 'startxref' marker.");                                  
                             355:        }                                                                                          
                             356:        else                                                                                       
                             357:        {                                                                                          
                             358:            return skipBytes + bufOff;                                                             
                             359:        }                                                                                          
                             360:    }                                                                                              
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java:130-180                         
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             130:     * @throws IOException if something went wrong                                                 
                             131:     */                                                                                            
                             132:    private void bfSearchForObjects() throws IOException                                           
                             133:    {                                                                                              
                             134:        long lastEOFMarker = bfSearchForLastEOFMarker();                                           
                             135:        long originOffset = source.getPosition();                                                  
                             136:        long currentOffset = MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET;                                                
                             137:        long lastObjectId = Long.MIN_VALUE;                                                        
                             138:        int lastGenID = Integer.MIN_VALUE;                                                         
                             139:        long lastObjOffset = Long.MIN_VALUE;                                                       
                             140:        char[] endobjString = "ndo".toCharArray();                                                 
                             141:        char[] endobjRemainingString = "bj".toCharArray();                                         
                             142:        boolean endOfObjFound = false;                                                             
                             143:        do                                                                                         
                             144:        {                                                                                          
                             145:            source.seek(currentOffset);                                                            
                             146:            int nextChar = source.read();                                                          
                             147:            currentOffset++;                                                                       
                             148:            if (BaseParser.isWhitespace(nextChar) && parser.isString(OBJ_MARKER))                  
                             149:            {                                                                                      
                             150:                long tempOffset = currentOffset - 2;                                               
                             151:                source.seek(tempOffset);                                                           
                             152:                int genID = source.peek();                                                         
                             153:                // is the next char a digit?                                                       
                             154:                if (BaseParser.isDigit(genID))                                                     
                             155:                {                                                                                  
                             156:                    genID -= 48;                                                                   
                             157:                    tempOffset--;                                                                  
                             158:                    source.seek(tempOffset);                                                       
                             159:                    if (parser.isWhitespace())                                                     
                             160:                    {                                                                              
                             161:                        while (tempOffset > MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET &&                               
                             parser.isWhitespace())                                                                                 
                             162:                        {                                                                          
                             163:                            source.seek(--tempOffset);                                             
                             164:                        }                                                                          
                             165:                        boolean objectIDFound = false;                                             
                             166:                        while (tempOffset > MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET &&                               
                             parser.isDigit())                                                                                      
                             167:                        {                                                                          
                             168:                            source.seek(--tempOffset);                                             
                             169:                            objectIDFound = true;                                                  
                             170:                        }                                                                          
                             171:                        if (objectIDFound)                                                         
                             172:                        {                                                                          
                             173:                            source.read();                                                         
                             174:                            long objectId = parser.readObjectNumber();                             
                             175:                            if (lastObjOffset > 0)                                                 
                             176:                            {                                                                      
                             177:                                // add the former object ID only if there was a                    
                             subsequent object ID                                                                                   
                             178:                                bfSearchCOSObjectKeyOffsets.put(                                   
                             179:                                        new COSObjectKey(lastObjectId, lastGenID),                 
                             lastObjOffset);                                                                                        
                             180:                            }                                                                      
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/COSParser.java:400-450                                
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             400:                                                                                                   
                             401:    /**                                                                                            
                             402:     * Return true if parser is lenient. Meaning auto healing capacity of the                      
                             parser are used.                                                                                       
                             403:     *                                                                                             
                             404:     * @return true if parser is lenient                                                           
                             405:     */                                                                                            
                             406:    public boolean isLenient()                                                                     
                             407:    {                                                                                              
                             408:        return isLenient;                                                                          
                             409:    }                                                                                              
                             410:                                                                                                   
                             411:    /**                                                                                            
                             412:     * Change the parser leniency flag.                                                            
                             413:     *                                                                                             
                             414:     * This method can only be called before the parsing of the file.                              
                             415:     *                                                                                             
                             416:     * @param lenient try to handle malformed PDFs.                                                
                             417:     *                                                                                             
                             418:     */                                                                                            
                             419:    protected void setLenient(boolean lenient)                                                     
                             420:    {                                                                                              
                             421:        if (initialParseDone)                                                                      
                             422:        {                                                                                          
                             423:            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Cannot change leniency after                       
                             parsing");                                                                                             
                             424:        }                                                                                          
                             425:        this.isLenient = lenient;                                                                  
                             426:    }                                                                                              
                             427:                                                                                                   
                             428:    @Override                                                                                      
                             429:    public COSBase dereferenceCOSObject(COSObject obj) throws IOException                          
                             430:    {                                                                                              
                             431:        long currentPos = source.getPosition();                                                    
                             432:        COSObjectKey key = obj.getKey();                                                           
                             433:        COSBase parsedObj = parseObjectDynamically(key, false);                                    
                             434:        if (parsedObj != null)                                                                     
                             435:        {                                                                                          
                             436:            parsedObj.setDirect(false);                                                            
                             437:            parsedObj.setKey(key);                                                                 
                             438:        }                                                                                          
                             439:        if (currentPos > 0)                                                                        
                             440:        {                                                                                          
                             441:            source.seek(currentPos);                                                               
                             442:        }                                                                                          
                             443:        return parsedObj;                                                                          
                             444:    }                                                                                              
                             445:                                                                                                   
                             446:    @Override                                                                                      
                             447:    public RandomAccessReadView createRandomAccessReadView(long startPosition,                     
                             long streamLength)                                                                                     
                             448:            throws IOException                                                                     
                             449:    {                                                                                              
                             450:        return source.createView(startPosition, streamLength);                                     
                             ```

                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/COSParser.java:793-885                                
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             793:    private long readUntilEndStream(final EndstreamFilterStream out) throws                        
                             IOException                                                                                            
                             794:    {                                                                                              
                             795:        int bufSize;                                                                               
                             796:        int charMatchCount = 0;                                                                    
                             797:        byte[] keyw = ENDSTREAM;                                                                   
                             798:                                                                                                   
                             799:        // last character position of shortest keyword ('endobj')                                  
                             800:        final int quickTestOffset = 5;                                                             
                             801:                                                                                                   
                             802:        // read next chunk into buffer; already matched chars are added to                         
                             beginning of buffer                                                                                    
                             803:        while ( ( bufSize = source.read( strmBuf, charMatchCount, STRMBUFLEN -                     
                             charMatchCount ) ) > 0 )                                                                               
                             804:        {                                                                                          
                             805:            bufSize += charMatchCount;                                                             
                             806:                                                                                                   
                             807:            int bIdx = charMatchCount;                                                             
                             808:            int quickTestIdx;                                                                      
                             809:                                                                                                   
                             810:            // iterate over buffer, trying to find keyword match                                   
                             811:            for ( int maxQuicktestIdx = bufSize - quickTestOffset; bIdx < bufSize;                 
                             bIdx++ )                                                                                               
                             812:            {                                                                                      
                             813:                // reduce compare operations by first test last character we would                 
                             have to                                                                                                
                             814:                // match if current one matches; if it is not a character from                     
                             keywords                                                                                               
                             815:                // we can move behind the test character; this shortcut is                         
                             inspired by the                                                                                        
                             816:                // Boyer-Moore string search algorithm and can reduce parsing time                 
                             by approx. 20%                                                                                         
                             817:                quickTestIdx = bIdx + quickTestOffset;                                             
                             818:                if (charMatchCount == 0 && quickTestIdx < maxQuicktestIdx)                         
                             819:                {                                                                                  
                             820:                    final byte ch = strmBuf[quickTestIdx];                                         
                             821:                    if ( ( ch > 't' ) || ( ch < 'a' ) )                                            
                             822:                    {                                                                              
                             823:                        // last character we would have to match if current                        
                             character would match                                                                                  
                             824:                        // is not a character from keywords -> jump behind and                     
                             start over                                                                                             
                             825:                        bIdx = quickTestIdx;                                                       
                             826:                        continue;                                                                  
                             827:                    }                                                                              
                             828:                }                                                                                  
                             829:                                                                                                   
                             830:                // could be negative - but we only compare to ASCII                                
                             831:                final byte ch = strmBuf[bIdx];                                                     
                             832:                                                                                                   
                             833:                if ( ch == keyw[ charMatchCount ] )                                                
                             834:                {                                                                                  
                             835:                    if ( ++charMatchCount == keyw.length )                                         
                             836:                    {                                                                              
                             837:                        // match found                                                             
                             838:                        bIdx++;                                                                    
                             839:                        break;                                                                     
                             840:                    }                                                                              
                             841:                }                                                                                  
                             842:                else                                                                               
                             843:                {                                                                                  
                             844:                    if ( ( charMatchCount == 3 ) && ( ch == ENDOBJ[ charMatchCount                 
                             ] ) )                                                                                                  
                             845:                    {                                                                              
                             846:                        // maybe ENDSTREAM is missing but we could have ENDOBJ                     
                             847:                        keyw = ENDOBJ;                                                             
                             848:                        charMatchCount++;                                                          
                             849:                    }                                                                              
                             850:                    else                                                                           
                             851:                    {                                                                              
                             852:                        // no match; incrementing match start by 1 would be dumb                   
                             since we already know                                                                                  
                             853:                        // matched chars depending on current char read we may                     
                             already have beginning                                                                                 
                             854:                        // of a new match: 'e': first char matched; 'n': if we are                 
                             at match position                                                                                      
                             855:                        // idx 7 we already read 'e' thus 2 chars matched for each                 
                             other char we have                                                                                     
                             856:                        // to start matching first keyword char beginning with                     
                             next read position                                                                                     
                             857:                        charMatchCount = ( ch == E ) ? 1 : ( ( ch == N ) && (                      
                             charMatchCount == 7 ) ) ? 2 : 0;                                                                       
                             858:                        // search again for 'endstream'                                            
                             859:                        keyw = ENDSTREAM;                                                          
                             860:                    }                                                                              
                             861:                }                                                                                  
                             862:            }                                                                                      
                             863:                                                                                                   
                             864:            int contentBytes = Math.max( 0, bIdx - charMatchCount );                               
                             865:                                                                                                   
                             866:            // write buffer content until first matched char to output stream                      
                             867:            if ( contentBytes > 0 )                                                                
                             868:            {                                                                                      
                             869:                out.filter(strmBuf, 0, contentBytes);                                              
                             870:            }                                                                                      
                             871:            if ( charMatchCount == keyw.length )                                                   
                             872:            {                                                                                      
                             873:                // keyword matched; unread matched keyword (endstream/endobj) and                  
                             following buffered content                                                                             
                             874:                source.rewind( bufSize - contentBytes );                                           
                             875:                break;                                                                             
                             876:            }                                                                                      
                             877:            else                                                                                   
                             878:            {                                                                                      
                             879:                // copy matched chars at start of buffer                                           
                             880:                System.arraycopy( keyw, 0, strmBuf, 0, charMatchCount );                           
                             881:            }                                                                                      
                             882:        }                                                                                          
                             883:        // this writes a lonely CR or drops trailing CR LF and LF                                  
                             884:        return out.calculateLength();                                                              
                             885:    }                                                                                              
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFStreamParser.java:78-87                            
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             78:    public List<Object> parse() throws IOException                                                  
                             79:    {                                                                                               
                             80:        List<Object> streamObjects = new ArrayList<>(100);                                          
                             81:        Object token;                                                                               
                             82:        while( (token = parseNextToken()) != null )                                                 
                             83:        {                                                                                           
                             84:            streamObjects.add( token );                                                             
                             85:        }                                                                                           
                             86:        return streamObjects;                                                                       
                             87:    }                                                                                               
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFStreamParser.java:96-107                           
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             96:    public Object parseNextToken() throws IOException                                               
                             97:    {                                                                                               
                             98:        if (source.isClosed())                                                                      
                             99:        {                                                                                           
                             100:            return null;                                                                           
                             101:        }                                                                                          
                             102:        skipSpaces();                                                                              
                             103:        if (source.isEOF())                                                                        
                             104:        {                                                                                          
                             105:            close();                                                                               
                             106:            return null;                                                                           
                             107:        }                                                                                          
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFStreamParser.java:286-304                          
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             286:                // until EI<whitespace>.                                                           
                             287:                // Be aware not all kind of whitespaces are allowed here. see                      
                             PDFBOX-1561                                                                                            
                             288:                while( !(lastByte == 'E' &&                                                        
                             289:                         currentByte == 'I' &&                                                     
                             290:                         hasNextSpaceOrReturn() &&                                                 
                             291:                    hasNoFollowingBinData()) &&                                                    
                             292:                    !isEOF())                                                                      
                             293:                {                                                                                  
                             294:                    imageData.write( lastByte );                                                   
                             295:                    lastByte = currentByte;                                                        
                             296:                    currentByte = source.read();                                                   
                             297:                }                                                                                  
                             298:                // the EI operator isn't unread, as it won't be processed anyway                   
                             299:                Operator beginImageDataOP = Operator                                               
                             300:                        .getOperator(OperatorName.BEGIN_INLINE_IMAGE_DATA);                        
                             301:                // save the image data to the operator, so that it can be accessed                 
                             later                                                                                                  
                             302:                beginImageDataOP.setImageData(imageData.toByteArray());                            
                             303:                return beginImageDataOP;                                                           
                             304:            case ']':                                                                              
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFStreamParser.java:330-402                          
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             330:    private boolean hasNoFollowingBinData() throws IOException                                     
                             331:    {                                                                                              
                             332:        // as suggested in PDFBOX-1164                                                             
                             333:        final int readBytes = source.read(binCharTestArr, 0,                                       
                             MAX_BIN_CHAR_TEST_LENGTH);                                                                             
                             334:        boolean noBinData = true;                                                                  
                             335:        int startOpIdx = -1;                                                                       
                             336:        int endOpIdx = -1;                                                                         
                             337:        String s = "";                                                                             
                             338:                                                                                                   
                             339:        LOG.debug("String after EI: '{}'", () -> new String(binCharTestArr));                      
                             340:                                                                                                   
                             341:        if (readBytes > 0)                                                                         
                             342:        {                                                                                          
                             343:            for (int bIdx = 0; bIdx < readBytes; bIdx++)                                           
                             344:            {                                                                                      
                             345:                final byte b = binCharTestArr[bIdx];                                               
                             346:                if (b != 0 && b < 0x09 || b > 0x0a && b < 0x20 && b != 0x0d)                       
                             347:                {                                                                                  
                             348:                    // control character or > 0x7f -> we have binary data                          
                             349:                    noBinData = false;                                                             
                             350:                    break;                                                                         
                             351:                }                                                                                  
                             352:                // find the start of a PDF operator                                                
                             353:                if (startOpIdx == -1 && !(b == 0 || b == 9 || b == 0x20 || b ==                    
                             0x0a || b == 0x0d))                                                                                    
                             354:                {                                                                                  
                             355:                    startOpIdx = bIdx;                                                             
                             356:                }                                                                                  
                             357:                else if (startOpIdx != -1 && endOpIdx == -1 &&                                     
                             358:                         (b == 0 || b == 9 || b == 0x20 || b == 0x0a || b ==                       
                             0x0d))                                                                                                 
                             359:                {                                                                                  
                             360:                    endOpIdx = bIdx;                                                               
                             361:                }                                                                                  
                             362:            }                                                                                      
                             363:                                                                                                   
                             364:            // PDFBOX-3742: just assuming that 1-3 non blanks is a PDF operator                    
                             isn't enough                                                                                           
                             365:            if (noBinData && endOpIdx != -1 && startOpIdx != -1)                                   
                             366:            {                                                                                      
                             367:                // usually, the operator here is Q, sometimes EMC (PDFBOX-2376), S                 
                             (PDFBOX-3784),                                                                                         
                             368:                // or a number (PDFBOX-5957)                                                       
                             369:                s = new String(binCharTestArr, startOpIdx, endOpIdx - startOpIdx);                 
                             370:                if (!"Q".equals(s) && !"EMC".equals(s) && !"S".equals(s) &&                        
                             371:                    !s.matches("^\\d*\\.?\\d*$"))                                                  
                             372:                {                                                                                  
                             373:                    // operator is not Q, not EMC, not S, nur a number -> assume                   
                             binary data                                                                                            
                             374:                    noBinData = false;                                                             
                             375:                }                                                                                  
                             376:            }                                                                                      
                             377:                                                                                                   
                             378:            // only if not close to EOF                                                            
                             379:            if (noBinData && startOpIdx != -1 && readBytes ==                                      
                             MAX_BIN_CHAR_TEST_LENGTH)                                                                              
                             380:            {                                                                                      
                             381:                if (endOpIdx == -1)                                                                
                             382:                {                                                                                  
                             383:                    endOpIdx = MAX_BIN_CHAR_TEST_LENGTH;                                           
                             384:                    s = new String(binCharTestArr, startOpIdx, endOpIdx -                          
                             startOpIdx);                                                                                           
                             385:                }                                                                                  
                             386:                LOG.debug("startOpIdx: {} endOpIdx: {} s = '{}'", startOpIdx,                      
                             endOpIdx, s);                                                                                          
                             387:                // look for token of 3 chars max or a number                                       
                             388:                if (endOpIdx - startOpIdx > 3 && !s.matches("^\\d*\\.?\\d*$"))                     
                             389:                {                                                                                  
                             390:                    noBinData = false; // "operator" too long, assume binary data                  
                             391:                }                                                                                  
                             392:            }                                                                                      
                             393:            source.rewind(readBytes);                                                              
                             394:        }                                                                                          
                             395:        if (!noBinData)                                                                            
                             396:        {                                                                                          
                             397:            LOG.warn(                                                                              
                             398:                    "ignoring 'EI' assumed to be in the middle of inline image at                  
                             stream offset {}, s = '{}'",                                                                           
                             399:                    source.getPosition(), s);                                                      
                             400:        }                                                                                          
                             401:        return noBinData;                                                                          
                             402:    }                                                                                              
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>                                                                                                 
                             pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java:524-560                         
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             524:    private long bfSearchForLastEOFMarker() throws IOException                                     
                             525:    {                                                                                              
                             526:        long lastEOFMarker = -1;                                                                   
                             527:        long originOffset = source.getPosition();                                                  
                             528:        source.seek(MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET);                                                        
                             529:        long tempMarker = findString(EOF_MARKER);                                                  
                             530:        while (tempMarker != -1)                                                                   
                             531:        {                                                                                          
                             532:            try                                                                                    
                             533:            {                                                                                      
                             534:                // check if the following data is some valid pdf content                           
                             535:                // which most likely indicates that the pdf is linearized,                         
                             536:                // updated or just cut off somewhere in the middle                                 
                             537:                parser.skipSpaces();                                                               
                             538:                if (!parser.isString(XREF_TABLE))                                                  
                             539:                {                                                                                  
                             540:                    parser.readObjectNumber();                                                     
                             541:                    parser.readGenerationNumber();                                                 
                             542:                }                                                                                  
                             543:            }                                                                                      
                             544:            catch (IOException exception)                                                          
                             545:            {                                                                                      
                             546:                // save the EOF marker as the following data is most likely some                   
                             garbage                                                                                                
                             547:                LOG.debug("An exception occurred during brute force for last EOF -                 
                             ignoring",                                                                                             
                             548:                        exception);                                                                
                             549:                lastEOFMarker = tempMarker;                                                        
                             550:            }                                                                                      
                             551:            tempMarker = findString(EOF_MARKER);                                                   
                             552:        }                                                                                          
                             553:        source.seek(originOffset);                                                                 
                             554:        // no EOF marker found                                                                     
                             555:        if (lastEOFMarker == -1)                                                                   
                             556:        {                                                                                          
                             557:            lastEOFMarker = Long.MAX_VALUE;                                                        
                             558:        }                                                                                          
                             559:        return lastEOFMarker;                                                                      
                             560:    }                                                                                              
                             ```                                                                                                    
                             </code>                                                                                                
                             <code>

                             ```                                                                                                    
                             101:        //lastPrev prevents potential infinite loops in crafted files

                             103:        // ---- parse whole chain of xref tables/object streams using PREV

                             104:        COSDictionary trailer = null;
                             ```                                                                                                    

                             </code_snippets>                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                        
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                    
                             After reviewing the timeout report and the supplied parser code, it is clear that                      
                             several core parsing loops can spin for arbitrarily long when fed malformed or                         
                             truncated input. To prevent libFuzzer hangs (and thus ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout) we                  
                             must bound those loops with sensible, configurable thresholds that cause the parser to                 
                             bail out quickly on pathological data, while preserving correct behavior on                            
                             well-formed PDFs. We will introduce three targeted fixes:                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             1. Bound the stream-data search for endstream in COSParser.readUntilEndStream                        
                             2. Bound the inline-image data search for EI in PDFStreamParser                                      
                             3. Bound the brute-force search for %%EOF in BruteForceParser                                        
                                                                                                                                    
                             All bounds will be configurable via system properties (with defaults large enough not                  
                             to impact genuine documents) and will throw an IOException when exceeded, allowing the                 
                             fuzz harness to recover and move on.                                                                   
                                                                                                                                    
                              Detailed Steps                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                    
                             1. Introduce a maximum-length threshold for readUntilEndStream                                         
                                a. In COSParser (or BaseParser if thats where readUntilEndStream resides), add:                    
                                    A static default constant, e.g.                                                                
                                     `private static final long DEFAULT_MAX_STREAM_SEARCH = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10                 
                             MB`                                                                                                    
                                    A new instance field, initialized from a system property, e.g.                                 
                                     `maxStreamSearch = Long.getLong("pdfbox.parser.maxStreamSearch",                               
                             DEFAULT_MAX_STREAM_SEARCH);`                                                                           
                                b. In readUntilEndStream (around line 793), track the cumulative bytes scanned:                     
                                   ```java                                                                                          
                                   long totalScanned = 0;                                                                           
                                   while ((bufSize = source.read(...)) > 0) {                                                       
                                       totalScanned += bufSize;                                                                     
                                       if (totalScanned > maxStreamSearch) {                                                        
                                           throw new IOException("Exceeded maxStreamSearch (" + maxStreamSearch +                   
                             ") before 'endstream'");                                                                               
                                       }                                                                                            
                                       // existing keyword-matching logic                                                          
                                   }                                                                                                
                                   ```                                                                                              
                                c. This ensures that a missing or corrupted endstream does not drive an unbounded                 
                             loop.                                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                    
                             2. Introduce a maximum-length threshold for inline-image data                                          
                                a. In PDFStreamParser, define a default maximum inline-image length, e.g.                           
                                   `private static final int DEFAULT_MAX_INLINE_IMAGE = 5 * 1024 * 1024; // 5 MB`                   
                                   and read it via a system property:                                                               
                                   `maxInlineImage = Integer.getInteger("pdfbox.parser.maxInlineImage",                             
                             DEFAULT_MAX_INLINE_IMAGE);`                                                                            
                                b. In the ID case (around lines 282297), before entering the while loop:                         
                                   ```java                                                                                          
                                   int inlineScanned = 0;                                                                           
                                   while (/* existing EI-detection condition */ && !isEOF()) {                                      
                                       if (++inlineScanned > maxInlineImage) {                                                      
                                           LOG.warn("Inline image data exceeded {} bytes at offset {}, aborting                     
                             image parse",                                                                                          
                                                    maxInlineImage, source.getPosition());                                          
                                           break;  // or throw IOException to stop parsing                                          
                                       }                                                                                            
                                       imageData.write(lastByte);                                                                   
                                       lastByte = currentByte;                                                                      
                                       currentByte = source.read();                                                                 
                                   }                                                                                                
                                   ```                                                                                              
                                c. This prevents endless reads when EI is never found.                                            
                                                                                                                                    
                             3. Limit the brute-force %%EOF search window                                                         
                                a. Add a getter in COSParser to expose the existing readTrailBytes (used in                         
                             startxref logic):                                                                                      
                                   ```java                                                                                          
                                   public int getEOFLookupRange() {                                                                 
                                       return readTrailBytes;                                                                       
                                   }                                                                                                
                                   ```                                                                                              
                                b. In BruteForceParser.bfSearchForLastEOFMarker (around lines 524530), replace the                 
                             open-ended scan with a confined window anchored at the file end. For example:                          
                                   ```java                                                                                          
                                   long fileLen = source.length();                                                                  
                                   long searchStart = Math.max(MINIMUM_SEARCH_OFFSET, fileLen -                                     
                             parser.getEOFLookupRange());                                                                           
                                   source.seek(searchStart);                                                                        
                                   long tempMarker = findString(EOF_MARKER);                                                        
                                   // no more while-loop over the entire file,                                                      
                                   // only accept the first occurrence in the trailing window.                                      
                                   if (tempMarker != -1) {                                                                          
                                       lastEOFMarker = tempMarker;                                                                  
                                   }                                                                                                
                                   // else leave lastEOFMarker at -1                                                                
                                   source.seek(originOffset);                                                                       
                                   ```                                                                                              
                                c. If no marker is found within that bounded window, BFParser will treat it as                      
                             missing and proceedavoiding a full-file scan.                                                         
                                                                                                                                    
                              Justification and Safeguards                                                                      
                              By mirroring the existing pattern used for startxref (readTrailBytes) and by                       
                             making all limits configurable system properties, we preserve current PDF parsing                      
                             behavior on valid files while imposing practical ceilings on malformed inputs.                         
                              Throwing IOExceptions on exceeded thresholds cleanly aborts the problematic parse                    
                             path and returns control to the harness without risk of silently skipping or                           
                             corrupting functionality.                                                                              
                              The defaults (10 MB for streams, 5 MB for inline images, existing EOF lookup range                   
                             for brute-force search) are high enough to accommodate large but valid PDF constructs;                 
                             users encountering false positives can tune the thresholds as needed.                                  
                              No fuzz harness or external libraries are touched. All changes reside in parser                      
                             internals. Existing tests should still pass, and any slow tests caused by extremely                    
                             large streams will now similarly abort faster.                                                         
                              This approach parallels other PDFBox safeguards (e.g., readTrailBytes) and follows                   
                             established code patterns, ensuring minimal risk of regressions.                                       
                              End of Strategy                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                    
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                        
                             ===Evaluation End===
