                                      private PageIterator(COSDictionary node)                                                      
                                      {                                                                                             
                             +            // Initialize cycle detection                                                             
                             +            visited.clear();

                                          while (!kids.isEmpty())                                                                   
                                          {                                                                                         
                             @@ -205,13 +208,26 @@

                                      private List<COSDictionary> enqueueKids(COSDictionary node)                                   
                                      {                                                                                             
                             +            if (node == null || !visited.add(node))                                                   
                             +            {                                                                                         
                             +                return Collections.emptyList();                                                       
                             +            }                                                                                         
                                          if (isPageTreeNode(node))                                                                 
                                          {                                                                                         
                             -                return getKids(node);                                                                 
                             +                List<COSDictionary> kids = getKids(node);                                             
                             +                List<COSDictionary> filtered = new ArrayList<>();                                     
                             +                for (COSDictionary kid : kids)                                                        
                             +                {                                                                                     
                             +                    if (visited.add(kid))                                                             
                             +                    {                                                                                 
                             +                        filtered.add(kid);                                                            
                             +                    }                                                                                 
                             +                }                                                                                     
                             +                return filtered;

                             @@ -221,7 +237,7 @@

                             node.getCOSName(COSName.TYPE)));

                             ===Patch Result===                                                                                     
                                                                                                                                    
                             ===Issue===                                                                                            
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Summary                                                                                             
                             The fuzzer run against PDFBox encounters a libFuzzer timeout. The initial issue is                     
                             that parsing certain inputs causes the fuzzer target to hang. An attempted patch adds                  
                             a configurable byte limit (`pdfbox.parser.maxCOSDictBytes`) to the                                     
                             `readUntilEndOfCOSDictionary` loop in `BaseParser.java`, logging a warning and                         
                             aborting recovery when the scan exceeds the limit. After applying this patch, the                      
                             fuzzer still times out. A JVM thread dump shows the main thread stuck in PDF page                      
                             traversal (`PDPageTree.getKids` and `PDFTextStripper.processPages`).                                   
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Description                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                    
                             1. Initial Issue                                                                                       
                                - Fuzzer output reports `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`, indicating the target hangs or                 
                             runs too long.                                                                                         
                                - No exception or error message beyond the timeout.                                                 
                                - The hang occurs during PDF parsing and text extraction                                            
                             (`PDFTextStripper.getText`) in the fuzz target.                                                        
                                                                                                                                    
                             2. Observations from Initial Issue                                                                     
                                - The fuzzer main thread is consuming CPU but makes no visible progress.                            
                                - Stack trace points to `traceCmpInt` (a coverage callback) then into page tree                     
                             iteration and text stripper.                                                                           
                                - Threads other than main are idle or performing JVM housekeeping.                                
                                                                                                                                    
                             3. Patch Attempt in `BaseParser.java`                                                                  
                                - Introduced two new variables at the top of `readUntilEndOfCOSDictionary()`:                       
                                   `maxDictScan` read from system property `pdfbox.parser.maxCOSDictBytes`                         
                             (default 1 MB).                                                                                        
                                   `dictScanned` as a counter.                                                                     
                                - Modified the existing loop condition                                                              
                                    while (c != -1 && c != '/' && c != '>' && dictScanned++ < maxDictScan)                          
                                - After the loop, if `dictScanned >= maxDictScan`, the method logs a warning and                    
                             returns `true` to abort dictionary recovery.                                                           
                                - The intent is to prevent extremely long or infinite loops when scanning COS                       
                             dictionaries.                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                    
                             4. Result After Applying the Patch                                                                     
                                - Fuzzer still reports `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`.                                                 
                                - The thread dump shows the main thread busy in:                                                    
                                     com.code_intelligence.jazzer.runtime.TraceDataFlowNativeCallbacks.traceCmpInt                 
                                     org.apache.pdfbox.pdmodel.PDPageTree.getKids                                                  
                                     org.apache.pdfbox.text.PDFTextStripper.processPages / writeText / getText                     
                                     com.example.PDFExtractTextFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput                                           
                                - No warning from the new log statement appears in the output, suggesting either                    
                             the limit was not reached or the code path was not exercised.                                          
                                                                                                                                    
                             5. Areas for Further Investigation                                                                     
                                - Code paths in `PDFTextStripper` and `PDPageTree` that handle page iteration and                   
                             stream extraction.                                                                                     
                                - Behavior of `readUntilEndOfCOSDictionary` when encountering deeply nested or                      
                             malformed dictionariesverify if it is actually invoked on the problematic input.                      
                                - Interaction between the parser recovery logic and the page tree traversal to                      
                             understand where control is stuck.                                                                     
                                - Any other unbounded loops or recursion in downstream parsing (e.g., object stream                 
                             parsing, cross-reference table recovery).                                                              
                                - Configuration and default values of the new `pdfbox.parser.maxCOSDictBytes`                       
                             property to ensure the patch is active during fuzzing.                                                 
                                                                                                                                    
                             ## Initial Issue Log                                                                                   
                             Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                                         
                             <issue>                                                                                                
                             ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             </issue>

                             ```                                                                                                    
                             137:     * @return list of kids

                             139:    private List<COSDictionary> getKids(COSDictionary node)                                        
                             140:    {                                                                                              
                             141:        List<COSDictionary> result = new ArrayList<>();                                            
                             142:                                                                                                   
                             143:        COSArray kids = node.getCOSArray(COSName.KIDS);                                            
                             ```

                             ```                                                                                                    
                             182:        private final Queue<COSDictionary> queue = new ArrayDeque<>();                             
                             183:                                                                                                   
                             184:        private PageIterator(COSDictionary node)                                                   
                             185:        {                                                                                          
                             186:            List<COSDictionary> kids = enqueueKids(node);                                          
                             187:            while (!kids.isEmpty())

                             190:

                             204:         * @return                                                                                 
                             205:         */

                             207:        {                                                                                          
                             208:            if (isPageTreeNode(node))                                                              
                             209:            {

                             211:            }                                                                                      
                             212:            else                                                                                   
                             213:            {                                                                                      
                             214:                if (node != null &&                                                                
                             COSName.PAGE.equals(node.getCOSName(COSName.TYPE)))                                                    
                             215:                {                                                                                  
                             216:                    queue.add(node);                                                               
                             217:                }                                                                                  
                             218:                else                                                                               
                             219:                {                                                                                  
                             220:                    LOG.error("Page skipped due to an invalid or missing type {}",                 
                             221:                            () -> (node == null ? "(null)" :                                       
                             node.getCOSName(COSName.TYPE)));                                                                       
                             222:                }                                                                                  
                             223:            }                                                                                      
                             224:            return Collections.EMPTY_LIST;                                                         
                             225:        }                                                                                          
                             226:                                                                                                   
                             227:        @Override                                                                                  
                             228:        public boolean hasNext()                                                                   
                             229:        {                                                                                          
                             230:            return !queue.isEmpty();                                                               
                             231:        }                                                                                          
                             232:                                                                                                   
                             233:        @Override                                                                                  
                             234:        public PDPage next()                                                                       
                             235:        {                                                                                          
                             ```

                             ```                                                                                                    
                             243:
                             ```                                                                                                    

                             ```                                                                                                    
                             262:    protected void processPages(PDPageTree pages) throws IOException                               
                             263:    {                                                                                              
                             264:        PDPage startBookmarkPage = startBookmark == null ? null                                    
                             265:                : startBookmark.findDestinationPage(document);                                     
                             266:        if (startBookmarkPage != null)                                                             
                             267:        {                                                                                          
                             268:            startBookmarkPageNumber = pages.indexOf(startBookmarkPage) + 1;                        
                             269:        }                                                                                          
                             270:        else                                                                                       
                             271:        {                                                                                          
                             272:            // -1 = undefined                                                                      
                             273:            startBookmarkPageNumber = -1;                                                          
                             274:        }                                                                                          
                             275:                                                                                                   
                             276:        PDPage endBookmarkPage = endBookmark == null ? null                                        
                             277:                : endBookmark.findDestinationPage(document);                                       
                             278:        if (endBookmarkPage != null)                                                               
                             279:        {                                                                                          
                             280:            endBookmarkPageNumber = pages.indexOf(endBookmarkPage) + 1;                            
                             281:        }                                                                                          
                             282:        else                                                                                       
                             283:        {                                                                                          
                             284:            // -1 = undefined                                                                      
                             285:            endBookmarkPageNumber = -1;                                                            
                             286:        }                                                                                          
                             287:                                                                                                   
                             288:        if (startBookmarkPageNumber == -1 && startBookmark != null &&                              
                             endBookmarkPageNumber == -1                                                                            
                             289:                && endBookmark != null                                                             
                             290:                && startBookmark.getCOSObject() == endBookmark.getCOSObject())                     
                             291:        {                                                                                          
                             292:            // this is a special case where both the start and end bookmark                        
                             293:            // are the same but point to nothing. In this case                                     
                             294:            // we will not extract any text.                                                       
                             295:            startBookmarkPageNumber = 0;                                                           
                             296:            endBookmarkPageNumber = 0;                                                             
                             297:        }                                                                                          
                             298:                                                                                                   
                             299:        for (PDPage page : pages)                                                                  
                             300:        {                                                                                          
                             301:            if (page.hasContents())                                                                
                             302:            {                                                                                      
                             303:                processPage(page);                                                                 
                             304:            }                                                                                      
                             305:            currentPageNo++;                                                                       
                             306:        }                                                                                          
                             307:    }                                                                                              
                             ```

                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                        
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                    
                             1. Summary of the root cause                                                                           
                                - The libFuzzer timeout is ultimately caused by an infinite loop in                                 
                             PDPageTree.PageIterators constructor (lines 184197). When traversing a malformed PDF                 
                             whose page-tree nodes reference ancestors or form cycles, the `while                                   
                             (!kids.isEmpty())` loop never terminates because there is no cycle detection. The                      
                             patch in BaseParser.java did not hit this code path and therefore did not resolve the                  
                             hang.                                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                    
                             2. High-level approach                                                                                 
                                - Introduce cycle detection in the page-tree traversal so that each COSDictionary                   
                             node is visited at most once. Once a node is seen, further attempts to enqueue it will                 
                             be skipped, guaranteeing that the `kids` list eventually empties and the constructors                 
                             loop terminates.                                                                                       
                                - Reapply (and keep) the previous `readUntilEndOfCOSDictionary` patch (the                          
                             configurable `maxCOSDictBytes` limit) because it still helps guard against unbounded                   
                             dictionary-scanning loops, even though it did not impact this particular hang.                         
                                                                                                                                    
                             3. Detailed patch plan                                                                                 
                                A. In PDPageTree.java                                                                               
                                a. Inside the inner class `PageIterator`, introduce a visited set and clear it at                 
                             the start of each iteration:                                                                           
                                    Option 1 (reuse existing field): call `pageSet.clear()` at the top of the                      
                             `PageIterator(COSDictionary node)` constructor.                                                        
                                    Option 2 (preferred for isolation): declare a private final                                    
                             `Set<COSDictionary> visited = new HashSet<>();` in `PageIterator`.                                     
                                                                                                                                    
                                b. Modify `enqueueKids(COSDictionary node)` to skip any node already in the visited                 
                             set:                                                                                                   
                                    At method entry, if `node == null` or `!visited.add(node)`, immediately return                 
                             `Collections.emptyList()`.                                                                             
                                    If `isPageTreeNode(node)`, call `getKids(node)` as before, then filter out                     
                             children where `visited.add(child)` returns falsei.e., only return unvisited                          
                             children.                                                                                              
                                    Else if its a leaf page (`COSName.PAGE`), add it to the queue only if it was                  
                             newly added to `visited`.                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                                c. The revised `PageIterator` constructor will then look conceptually like:                         
                                   ```                                                                                              
                                   PageIterator(COSDictionary rootNode) {                                                           
                                       visited.clear();               // reset per iteration                                        
                                       List<COSDictionary> kids = enqueueKids(rootNode);                                            
                                       while (!kids.isEmpty()) {                                                                    
                                           List<COSDictionary> newKids = new ArrayList<>();                                         
                                           for (COSDictionary kid : kids) {                                                         
                                               newKids.addAll(enqueueKids(kid));                                                    
                                           }                                                                                        
                                           kids = newKids;                                                                          
                                       }                                                                                            
                                   }                                                                                                
                                   ```                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                    
                                d. This ensures that each COSDictionary participates in the expansion at most once,                 
                             so the expansion loop always terminateseven under cycles.                                             
                                                                                                                                    
                                B. In BaseParser.java                                                                               
                                - Reapply the `pdfbox.parser.maxCOSDictBytes` guard in                                              
                             `readUntilEndOfCOSDictionary()` exactly as in the last patch attempt, to prevent                       
                             extraordinarily large dictionary scans elsewhere.                                                      
                                                                                                                                    
                             4. Why this approach                                                                                   
                                - **Targets the true hang**: instrumentation shows the fuzzer stuck in                              
                             `PDPageTree.getKids`/`PDFTextStripper.processPages`, not in dictionary scanning.                       
                             Introducing a visited set directly cuts off the infinite expansion.                                    
                                - **Minimal and safe**: only one class (PDPageTree) is modified, without touching                   
                             fuzz harness, logging, or other downstream logic.                                                      
                                - **Preserves semantics**: valid page trees (acyclic) are traversed in the same                     
                             breadth-first manner, with the same ordering of pages. Only pathological cycles are                    
                             broken.                                                                                                
                                - **Avoids over-broad fixes**: no global node limits or timeouts, no changes to                     
                             external libraries, no harness or test code changes.                                                   
                                                                                                                                    
                             5. Potential side-effects & mitigation                                                                 
                                - **Shared page dictionaries**: if a PDF legitimately reuses the same page object                   
                             in multiple parts of the tree, this will enqueue it only once. In practice, PDF page                   
                             re-use is extremely rare, and duplicate pages seldom intended.                                         
                                - **Index-of behavior**: PDFTextStrippers calls to `pages.indexOf(...)` may still                  
                             work correctly, because all unique pages are still enqueued once.                                      
                                - **Memory**: the visited set grows proportionally to the number of unique nodes;                   
                             this matches the original queue size and should not increase peak memory.                              
                                                                                                                                    
                             6. Verification                                                                                        
                                - **Unit test**: add or update a small test PDF with an artificial cycle in the                     
                             page tree; verify `PDPageTree.iterator()` terminates and returns pages once.                           
                                - **Fuzzer run**: rerun the jazzer/libFuzzer target against previously hanging                      
                             inputs; verify there is no timeout and the fuzzer reports coverage progress.                           
                                - **Regression tests**: run existing PDFBox test suite to ensure no behavior                        
                             changes on well-formed PDFs.                                                                           
                                                                                                                                    
                             7. References                                                                                          
                                - The unused `private final Set<COSDictionary> pageSet` declared on PDPageTree                      
                             (lines 5051) demonstrates intent to track pages; this patch gives it purpose.                         
                                - Similar cycle-detection patterns exist elsewhere in PDFBox (e.g., XRef table                      
                             recovery) and can serve as guidance on set-membership checks.                                          
                                                                                                                                    
                             </fix_strategy>
